type="user">hodge-theory-i-definition-1.1</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-i-definition-1.1.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>1.1</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-i-1</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A <fr:em>mixed Hodge structure</fr:em> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> consists of

    
 <html:ol
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(a) &quot;">
        a <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex>-module <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H_\mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex> of finite type (the "<fr:em>integer lattice</fr:em>");
      </html:li>

      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(b) &quot;">
        a finite increasing filtration <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[W]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H_\mathbb {Q}=H_\mathbb {Z}\otimes \mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex> (the "<fr:em>weight filtration</fr:em>");
      </html:li>

      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(c) &quot;">
        a finite decreasing filtration <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H_\mathbb {C}=H_\mathbb {Z}\otimes \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> (the "<fr:em>Hodge filtration</fr:em>").
      </html:li>

    </html:ol>


    This data is subject to the following condition:
    there exists a (unique) bigradation of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Gr}_W(H_\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex> by subspaces <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H^{p,q}]]></fr:tex> such that

    
 <html:ol
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(i) &quot;">
        <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Gr}_W^n(H_\mathbb {C})=\bigoplus _{p+q=n}H^{p,q}]]></fr:tex>
      </html:li>

      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(ii) &quot;">
        the filtration <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> induces on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Gr}_W(H_\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex> the filtration
        <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[           \operatorname {Gr}_W(F)^p           = \bigoplus _{p'\geq  p} H^{p',q'}         ]]></fr:tex>
      </html:li>

      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(iii) &quot;">
        <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\overline {H^{pq}}=H^{qp}]]></fr:tex>.
      </html:li>

    </html:ol></fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:p>A <fr:em>morphism</fr:em> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  H\to  H']]></fr:tex> is a homomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_\mathbb {Z}\colon  H_\mathbb {Z}\to  H'_\mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_\mathbb {Q}\colon  H_\mathbb {Q}\to  H'_\mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_\mathbb {C}\colon  H_\mathbb {C}\to  H'_\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> are compatible with the filtrations <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[W]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> (respectively).</fr:p><fr:tree
