type="user">hodge-theory-i-1.2</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-i-1.2.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>1.2</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-i-1</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The <fr:em>Hodge numbers</fr:em> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> are the integers
    <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[       h^{pq} = \dim  H^{pq} = h^{qp}.     \tag{1.2}     ]]></fr:tex></fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:p>We say that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> is pure <fr:em>of weight <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex></fr:em> if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[h^{pq}=0]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p+q\neq  n]]></fr:tex> (i.e. if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Gr}_W^i(H)=0]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i\neq  n]]></fr:tex>).
  We also say that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:em>Hodge structure of weight <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex></fr:em>.</fr:p><fr:p>The <fr:em>Tate Hodge structure</fr:em> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {Z}(1)]]></fr:tex> is the Hodge structure of weight <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[-2]]></fr:tex>, of pure degree <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(-1,-1)]]></fr:tex>, for which <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {Z}(1)_\mathbb {C}=\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {Z}(1)_\mathbb {Z} = 2\pi  i\mathbb {Z} = \operatorname {Ker}(\exp \colon \mathbb {C}\to \mathbb {C}^*)\subset \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>.
  We set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {Z}(n)=\mathbb {Z}(1)^{\otimes  n}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>We can show that mixed Hodge structures form an abelian category.
  If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  H\to  H']]></fr:tex> is a morphism, then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_\mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> are strictly compatible with the filtrations <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[W]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> (cf. <fr:link
type="local"
href="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.5.xml"
addr="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.5">[Hodge Theory II, 2.3.5]</fr:link>).</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>